<TITLE> Bangladesh sees 'new dawn of hope' in Obama presidency </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 20 (bdnew24.com)President Iajuddin Ahmed and Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina saw "a new dawn of hope" and partnership as Barack Obama became the 44th US president on Tuesday. "We, in Bangladesh, as many around the world, see in your leadership a new dawn of hope and we stand ready to extend to you our all-out cooperation," said Iajuddin in a congratulatory letter to Obama. "I, on behalf of the people of Bangladesh and on my own behalf, would like to extend to you our heartiest congratulations on your assumption of the office of the President of the United States of America." "I am confident that your inspiring and visionary leadership will steer your country at all times," said Iajuddin. Sheikh Hasina, in a separate message, said, "As you give the people of US a new beginning full of hope, we stand willing to work with you in a spirit of partnership. "You are aware that we have formed a government on 06 January 2009 on conclusion of free, fair and credible elections. "I am profoundly delighted at this happy coincidence," Hasina said. "I would also like to reiterate my government's commitment to closely work with you for further strengthening the friendly bilateral relations between our two countries, and to advance our common objectives," said the PM. Leader of the opposition Khaleda Zia also congratulated the new US president. "The multi-faceted relations between Bangladesh and the United States are excellent, time-tested and are based on the shared values and principles of democracy, human rights and the rule of law," said Kahleda. "I am confident these ties will grow in strength under your dynamic leadership," she said, according to a BNP press release. Foreign minister Dipu Moni told bdnews24.com: "I hope the existing friendly relations with the US will be enhanced." bdn
